President Donald J. Trump wrote an op-ed in the Washington Examiner highlighting his achievements in his first year in office. He mentions that the U.S. economy has grown at a rate of over 3 percent, with the creation of more than two million new jobs and a decrease in the unemployment rate to 4.1 percent. He also mentions the enactment of tax cuts and tax reform, aimed at simplifying and making the tax code fairer. Trump claims to have created a more business-friendly environment by eliminating regulations, exceeding the goal of eliminating two regulations for every new one. He emphasizes his efforts in rebuilding the military, implementing new national security strategies, and defeating ISIS. He also mentions the reforms made to improve healthcare and benefits for veterans. Finally, he highlights the appointments of judges who will interpret the law as written, including Supreme Court Justice Neil Gorsuch.